What would you tell your younger self?
Isn’t it nice to get dressed up once in a while? It’s amazing what a sparkly dress and jewelled heels can do for your mood! 🎉 
I spent my life as an athlete in skinsuits or baggy shorts, being shy about my muscular thighs and flat chest. I was even embarrassed about the fact I had defined abs 🙈 I didn’t go on holiday for over 10 years because I didn’t want people I didn’t even know to see me in a bikini. I look back and wish I could tell her how crazy that was and how amazing she looked. 
Your body holds so much more value than what you think other people are thinking about it- truth is nobody’s thinking anything. Nobody cares, most people are worrying about the same thing. Please love your body now. Don’t waste another day not enjoying yourself because of cellulite. Don’t look back in another 10 years and wish you’d talked to yourself more kindly. #enjoytoday #livelife #positiveselftalk

If you want to make progress in the gym then you gotta have a goal and you gotta make a plan. Be consistent, make it a priority, don’t let anyone stop you and never give up. #strong #mindset #motivated 
📸 @dankennedyphoto

A little Monday motivation- even if you only have 15 mins. Little and often, it does all add up! Don’t wait for a time in your life when you have and hour or two a day to dedicate to fitness to start that journey again. I am definitely goal driven but setting yourself up for failure with big lofty goals or an all or nothing mentality can be really overwhelming sometimes. Start with small process goals that you can tick off and achieve daily. Let yourself feel good about achieving those small wins and remind yourself of that positive feeling when you’re lacking motivation. 
If health and fitness goals of any size are achieved daily over a period of time then this will gradually become habit and more of a priority as you start to feel the benefits. 
Have a happy healthy Monday x
#mondaymotivation #coreworkout #fitinyour40s #roarfitness #london #dubai

As with any muscles you want to grow or make stronger there are a few basic key elements that somehow get forgotten so don’t over complicate things unnecessarily. 
Whatever phase you are at with your programme remember 3 things.
1) Challenge yourself. Lift as much weight as you can for the given rep range. Of course form is paramount but I see most people in the gym working in their comfort zone and not lifting to their strength capabilities. If it’s easy, your body won’t change.
2) If you want to grow you have to eat. If you are under fed you won’t perform, you won’t recover and you won’t max the benefits of training.
3) Sleep, sleep, sleep. Paramount for growth and recovery so prioritise your sleep. Don’t eat too late, avoid stimulants (this includes scrolling), and go to bed a little earlier if possible. 
Sounding bossy but it comes from a place of love 💕 Happy training! 
#armday #workout #weighttraining #strongwoman #dubaigym

Training tips-

Add unilateral exercises.
Train through lower rep ranges too.
Don’t forget lateral movements.

Isn’t every day leg day? 
People assume I train really hard but the truth is that little and often is key for me now.
Due to old sporting and accident injuries I do have to be quite careful not to aggravate old issues. My exercise pool that I can train heavy or to failure is quite limited but I am grateful for I am able to do. I try to keep my muscle stimulated enough to stay strong, maintain mass and keep lean. 
As an athlete I was training 6 hours per day, 6 days per week and that was ALL LEGS- no upper body work required! Now, 40 mins of weights 3x per week and a daily power walk keeps me where I want to be 🤗
Questions on training always welcome in comments ⬇️ 
#weighttraining #legday #workout #strongwomen

I’m back! Back at @roardubai and buzzing to get back to my training and nutrition routine. I am a creature of habit and although I’ve loved every second of my summer travels and I did stay pretty active, I want to get back to feeling my best.

Not sorry. Don’t let anyone tell you what you should or shouldn’t look like. I see people do this to each other all the time, especially when someone is making a positive lifestyle change resulting in weight loss. “You look great, but don’t lose any more” or “You’re becoming obsessed with the gym, you need a healthy balance” 🙄
I get it a lot, even now being considerably less muscular than I used to be. But I decided a long time ago, (when the DM online comments began), that I wasn’t going to care what people thought or said about me and I encourage you to do the same. It’s your body, your health, your future so do whatever you want to do and whatever makes you feel good ❤️ 
#fitnessrant #strongbodystrongmind #roarfitness #personaltraining

Yesterday I had a deliciously healthy organic chicken and cabbage Vietnamese salad for dinner. Today I ate 2500 kcals of peanut butter before 6am. Sometimes those damn hormones get the better of me 😆
Do I feel bad? Am I going to skips meals today? Am I going to train for 4 hours to regain a calorie deficit? No. No to all of the above. Do you think I look different tomorrow because I overate today? No again. 
My point is that if you do throw the balance out- please don’t stress. Just get back to your normal eating at your next meal and it won’t make a blind bit of difference I promise. 
#hormonal #balance #healthyfood #monthlycravings

Loving my @officialchilltubs !!
I’ve been doing ice baths daily for a year now and loving them more than ever. Until a couple of weeks ago I was carrying buckets of ice from a giant freezer in my garage but I wanted to make sure this wasn’t a short term practice before I got my Chill Tub. Of course it’s a shock to the system at first but you soon get used to it and it does make me feel great.
Before anyone says it’s easier in the sunshine- I completely agree with you 100% but I spent 15 years, 6-9 hours a day in and ice rink wearing Lycra. I had black toes from frostbite for 6 years straight so I served my time in the cold trust me 😆
Who’s tried? 
#icebath #chilltubs #coldwater #strongmind #coldwatertherapy

Yes I am a Personal Trainer and have been for 22 years. I am also a 3 x Olympic athlete and for the first time since I retired from sport I am using a coach again. 
It feels amazing to be on a structured and periodised training and nutrition plan designed by someone else. Someone I trust and someone who I know wants me to achieve as much as I do. It has taken any emotional decisions out so I am 100% doing what is right for my goals rather than just what I like doing and what I’m good at. 
Of course I am using a Roar Trainer coz they are the best. To be quite frank if they weren’t then they wouldn’t work here. 
Thank you @jbunting_roarfitness for putting up with me- my old skating coach knows your pain 😆 I will try to be better.
Time to level up! 💪🏻
